# scqubits Project Context

Superconducting qubit simulation library. Python >=3.9, BSD license.

## Class Hierarchy
- `QuantumSystem` (ABC) ‚Üí `QubitBaseClass` ‚Üí `QubitBaseClass1d` ‚Üí Transmon, Fluxonium
- `QuantumSystem` ‚Üí GenericQubit, Oscillator, KerrOscillator, Circuit
- All provide: `hamiltonian()`, `eigenvals()`, `eigensys()`, `hilbertdim()`, `truncated_dim`

## Key Modules
- `core/hilbert_space.py` ‚Äî `HilbertSpace` composites qubits+oscillators via QuTiP tensor products
- `core/diag.py` ‚Äî Pluggable eigensolvers: scipy, PRIMME, CuPy, JAX, cuQuantum. All in `DIAG_METHODS` dict.
- `core/param_sweep.py` ‚Äî `ParameterSweep` for multi-dim parameter scans with caching
- `core/noise.py` ‚Äî T1/Tphi decoherence calculations
- `core/central_dispatch.py` ‚Äî Event system for propagating parameter changes
- `settings.py` ‚Äî Global config: `NUM_CPUS`, `MULTIPROC`, `CUQUANTUM_*` Krylov params

## Dependencies
Core: numpy, scipy, qutip, matplotlib, sympy, pathos
GPU (optional): cupy, jax, cuquantum + qutip-cuquantum
